column22: So glad I got potter puppet pals as that last one

I think that for my personalized window, the algorithm did not fully align with my preferences. More than half of the recommended videos were related to the original video, though there were some songs included, so I guess the algorithm reacted to that. The personalized window was much better than the incognito window, though, because in incognito mode, the algorithm seemed to think I was a child and recommended some absurd videos that I genuinely would not watch. What I find interesting is that the videos recommended in incognito mode seemed more appropriate for 6-12-year-olds, but based on the "Duck Song," I would assume the viewer was a baby or toddler. So, the algorithm did not do a great job there either.

Although I am not a frequenter of the duck song, I did think it was interesting how similar the videos featured on my actual account and incognito mode were. I don't use YouTube that much compared to other social media platforms or other things that would have my algorithm, but I thought there would be more difference between the two algorithms.
I thought the experiment was pretty interesting, and I'm curious about the results. Looking forward to the findings of this research.
